        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 3:46PM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 346 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Flag Mountain, or 15 miles northwest of Hill City. This thunderstorm
was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rochford, Flag Mountain, Mystic, Deerfield, Deerfield Reservoir,
Crooks Tower, Roubaix Lake, and Black Fox Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
